Text:
I have met friends who have become strangers now and strangers who have become friends. Grateful for both kinds. Every person is a new book for me to explore, and everyone teaches me something new. I can't wait to discover more books, people, and their stories. 10/n.
n=10.
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text:
Shireen is beautiful, inside and out. And she will come back to this thread again when she has trouble remembering how beautiful life is on some days.
I want to be loved for who I am and not who I can be/cannot be. 9/n
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text:
You must be wondering, "As good as what or whom?"
By "as good", I mean efficient.
The conversations with my parents mostly used to be about what I cannot do more than what I can do. 
I want to remind myself to think about the latter more than the former. 8/n
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text: Having lived most of her life around people, who questioned her parents if they could be happier having an "abled" child or if they knew I had a disability before I was born, always made me (still makes me) feel that I can never be as good. 7/n
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text: I know that life isn't this beautiful every day, and some people decided to make the day less mundane for me, even though I seek happiness in mundane things. I hope Shireen grows into a strong, independent person while always being honest with her. 6/n
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text: Happy to sleep and spend a lot of time lying down in freshly washed sheets and plushies. I missed my mom when I thought how much she cared about the little things I liked, like sleeping on freshly cleaned sheets or giving me a head massage on my birthday. 5/n
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text: Another person bought me some fresh lemons because I love lemonade, and lemon tea, and just the smell of citrus fruits makes me happy. 4/n
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text:
A few people sent me beautiful messages which I responded to many hours late, happy that no one expects quick responses from me. 
Happy that no one gifted me things that I can't use, someone took care of the fact that my ink bottle was empty and they gifted me a refill. 3/n
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text: Felt so loved to share a yummy cake my friends bought. They did not disturb my sleep or rest and made sure I was ready to celebrate with them. Sometimes it's hard for me to be around many people, but today felt different and warm. 2/n
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text: Today is my birthday and I am so grateful for everything I got. I am grateful to be able to wake up and have a friend watch on me for a few hours when my caretaker wasn't around. Grateful to another friend to finish a task off my to-do list when I rested. 1/n
Name: Shireen Sultana

RT @chronicnotebook : How support your chronically ill or disabled friend
1. Research into their condition
2. Research ableism
3. Make accessible plans
4. Don't pressure them to do stuff while flaring
5. Ask before giving unsolicited advice
6. Offer to help with tasks
7. Understand it's unpredictable

Text:
@nehaa_sinha So we can see two hypothesis in our hand. The drongo hunts at night and not day:
1. to avoid competition
2. because it has already satiated its hunger
3. this behaviour has tuned their circadian rhythm
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text: That far surpasses any record in the articles. This late nocturnal habit is developing in urban areas, but predominantly nocturnal one is greatly surprising for me. @nehaa_sinha #birdingathome
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text:
My friend has seen them in West Bengal, but those footnotes describe it being observed in Chennai too. So can it be a wider phenomenon of ongoing evolution?
@nehaa_sinha #birdingathome
Name: Shireen Sultana

Text:
